.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-CHANNEL-GRAPH" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-channel-graph \- query the local channel graph
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-channel-graph
.RB [ --peer
.IR peer_id ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Returns edges from the local gossip channel graph via
.BR listchannels .
Use
.B --peer
to filter to channels involving a specific node.
.PP
Output:
.nf
[{source, destination, short_channel_id,
  base_fee_msat, fee_per_millionth, delay}]
.fi
Returns an empty array when the daemon is not reachable.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-route-find (1),
.BR lightning-channel-list (1)
